F. G. Wright and divers other persons whose names are unknown, to cheat and defraud such liege subjects of his Majesty the King as should be induced to purchase pictures in the belief that the said pictures were the genuine property of real judgment debtors whose goods had been seized in execution by the Sheriff upon judgments obtained in genuine actions brought against the said judgment debtors for the price of goods actually sold and delivered to them;
